column5: This is the last of them flew out today so I am back home and missing that place already. Finished the week with 21 different species.  The biggest being about a seven foot two hundred pound nurse shark.  Here's some shots off of the digital camera. Some cooler shotsa key deer on the bridgea gatorbig nurse sharksnowy grouperhog fishawesome tarpon shots good on the missus for the camera work.
i miss tarpon fishing so much already. Those bloody fish are insane
Wow man awesome!  Thanks for sharing?

Great report. It has me missing the place the family used to have in Charlotte Harbor. I went down for long weekends when I was working 12 hour shifts. We have great fishing right here but the unique thing about FLA whether fishing salt water or brackish water is you never know what you are going to hook into. From Sea Trout to Shark. I would use lighter tackle compared to the locals using 2X2's and chainfalls and always hooked up 3 times more than they did, and I lost a lot of tackle even using 100 pound flouro leaders.
